d=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2530986\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2530986\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Jan 04, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104pnr1665703136695.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/pnr1665703136695.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/pnr1665703136695.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"pnr1665703136695\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"pnr1665703136695__uxgetc_412043\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Get additional field data from the I/O buffer.</p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"pnr1665703136695__topic_d124925e1_d124926e1_d124927e1\">\n<div class=\"p\">\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104pnr1665703136695_html_0\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"pnr1665703136695__codeblock_mqc_4ql_bwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">short uxgetc (unsigned char*buffer, shortmax);</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"pnr1665703136695__topic_d88042e1_d88043e1_d88044e1_d88045e1_d88046e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d572859e61\">Parameters</h2>\n<dl class=\"dl parml\" id=\"pnr1665703136695__parml_rgb_pql_bwb\">\n<dt class=\"dt pt dlterm\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">buffer</var></dt>\n<dd class=\"dd pd\">Data from the I/O buffer (Output)</dd>\n<dt class=\"dt pt dlterm\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">max</var></dt>\n<dd class=\"dd pd\">Size of the buffer pointed to by <var class=\"keyword varname\">buffer</var>. This value should not\n                  be larger than the actual size of the buffer.</dd>\n</dl>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"pnr1665703136695__topic_d88047e1_d88048e1_d88049e1_d88050e1_d88051e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d572859e93\">Return Values</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"pnr1665703136695__table_d15017e1_d15018e1_d15019e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Values returned by uxgetc</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"pnr1665703136695__table_d15017e1_d15018e1_d15019e1__entry__1\">Value</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"pnr1665703136695__table_d15017e1_d15018e1_d15019e1__entry__2\">Meaning</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"pnr1665703136695__table_d15017e1_d15018e1_d15019e1__entry__1\">&gt;0</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"pnr1665703136695__table_d15017e1_d15018e1_d15019e1__entry__2\">The number of bytes copied into the\n                        buffer</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"pnr1665703136695__table_d15017e1_d15018e1_d15019e1__entry__1\">0</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"pnr1665703136695__table_d15017e1_d15018e1_d15019e1__entry__2\">An error occurred</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"pnr1665703136695__table_d15017e1_d15018e1_d15019e1__entry__1\">&lt;0</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"pnr1665703136695__table_d15017e1_d15018e1_d15019e1__entry__2\">The negated number of bytes copied into the\n                        buffer. The negative status indicates that more data is available in the I/O\n                        buffer, and that you should call <code class=\"ph codeph\">uxgetc</code> to get the\n                        additional data.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"pnr1665703136695__topic_d88052e1_d88053e1_d88054e1_d88055e1_d88056e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d572859e157\">Use</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"pnr1665703136695__d5947e20\">Library:  <span class=\"ph filepath\">yrtl</span>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"pnr1665703136695__topic_d88057e1_d88058e1_d88059e1_d88060e1_d88061e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d572859e170\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"pnr1665703136695__p_d124952e1_d124953e1_d124954e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">uxgetc</code> moves an additional chunk\n            of field data from the I/O buffer to the specified program buffer. This function should\n            be called only after a previous call to <code class=\"ph codeph\">uxget</code> or\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">uxgetc</code> returned a negative value, indicating there is more data\n            available.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"pnr1665703136695__p_d124955e1_d124956e1_d124957e1\">Parameters and return values are the same as for\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">uxget</code>. So if <code class=\"ph codeph\">uxgetc</code> returns a negative status, it\n            must be called repeatedly until a positive status is returned.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"pnr1665703136695__p_d124958e1_d124959e1_d124960e1\">Profile and subfield separator characters, if\n            present in a field, are also returned in the buffer, so you should be prepared to handle\n            these. For information about the representation of these characters, see the \"Subfield\n            Separator and Profile Characters\" topic.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"pnr1665703136695__section_dpj_wql_bwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d572859e199\">Example: uxget and uxgetc</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">The following example shows how to use <code class=\"ph codeph\">uxget</code> and\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">uxgetc</code> to obtain field data from the I/O buffer. Because the size of\n            the field is assumed unknown, we read fixed chunks and expand the buffer as necessary.\n            We use 100 as the size of the fixed chunks to read, although this is an arbitrary\n            choice.</p>\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104pnr1665703136695_html_1\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"pnr1665703136695__codeblock_olq_xql_bwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">#include &lt;h3gl.h&gt;\n#define CHUNKSIZE 100\n\nEXPORT int getbuffer ()\n{\nchar* buf;\nint len;\nint totlen;\n\nlen = uxget(buf, CHUNKSIZE); /* Get the first chunk of data */\ntotlen = abs(len); /* Set total length */\n\nwhile ( len &lt; 0 ) /* More to come */\n{\nbuf = realloc(buf, totlen+CHUNKSIZE); /* Make room for next chunk*/\nlen = uxgetc(buf+totlen, CHUNKSIZE); /* Read next chunk */\ntotlen += abs(len); /* Update total length */\n}\n\nreturn totlen;\n}</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/pan1665702658270.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Subfield Separator and Profile Characters</a><p>Uniface uses part of the reserved area of each meta character set (that is, the first 32 characters plus the last character) to store characters with special meaning within Uniface, such as subfield separators and profile characters.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/vtu1665703136625.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>uxget</a><p>Copy field data from the I/O buffer to the specified program buffer.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530986\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530986\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "uxgetc Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Jan 04, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Get additional field data from the I/O buffer. Explain this code short uxgetc (unsigned char*buffer, shortmax); Copy Parameters buffer Data from the I/O buffer (Output) max Size of the buffer pointed to by buffer . This value should not be larger than the actual size of the buffer. Return Values Table 1. Values returned by uxgetc Value Meaning >0 The number of bytes copied into the buffer 0 An error occurred <0 The negated number of bytes copied into the buffer. The negative status indicates that more data is available in the I/O buffer, and that you should call uxgetc to get the additional data. Use Library: yrtl Description uxgetc moves an additional chunk of field data from the I/O buffer to the specified program buffer. This function should be called only after a previous call to uxget or uxgetc returned a negative value, indicating there is more data available. Parameters and return values are the same as for uxget . So if uxgetc returns a negative status, it must be called repeatedly until a positive status is returned. Profile and subfield separator characters, if present in a field, are also returned in the buffer, so you should be prepared to handle these. For information about the representation of these characters, see the \"Subfield Separator and Profile Characters\" topic. Example: uxget and uxgetc The following example shows how to use uxget and uxgetc to obtain field data from the I/O buffer. Because the size of the field is assumed unknown, we read fixed chunks and expand the buffer as necessary. We use 100 as the size of the fixed chunks to read, although this is an arbitrary choice. Explain this code #include <h3gl.h> #define CHUNKSIZE 100 EXPORT int getbuffer () { char* buf; int len; int totlen; len = uxget(buf, CHUNKSIZE); /* Get the first chunk of data */ totlen = abs(len); /* Set total length */ while ( len < 0 ) /* More to come */ { buf = realloc(buf, totlen+CHUNKSIZE); /* Make room for next chunk*/ len = uxgetc(buf+totlen, CHUNKSIZE); /* Read next chunk */ totlen += abs(len); /* Update total length */ } return totlen; } Copy Related Links Subfield Separator and Profile Characters Uniface uses part of the reserved area of each meta character set (that is, the first 32 characters plus the last character) to store characters with special meaning within Uniface, such as subfield separators and profile characters. uxget Copy field data from the I/O buffer to the specified program buffer. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}